I was on the fence about seeing this movie in the theaters as I'd been so disappointed in TLJ.  Expecting to sit this one out, I listened to a ton of reviews including spoiler heavy analyses.  I broke down and saw it this morning and have to say that I really enjoyed it.  Went through 2 hankies!  Definitely the most emotional I've gotten watching the sequel trilogy and that's what makes this film stand out.  The criticisms are totally valid in terms of throwing everything in, breakneck pace, ret-cons, etc. but, my personal response was very positive.  [I actually think the spoiler heavy analyses I listened to beforehand helped me understand what was going on.]  I felt this was the first of the ST films that had the new characters front and center and they shone for me.  The chemistry that was so evident in the first act of TFA was on display here.  This conclusion really showed how negatively the left-turn made by Rian Johnson affected the trilogy.  Really wished this could have been broken into a Part I and Part II.  A truly pleasant surprise.
Tied together a lot of loose ends and closed some holes. A massive undertaking.

A little fast paced but overall a good movie. There's not a dull moment in it. Hopefully some books come out to help make sense of some things. The worst part of the movie experience was the 35 minutes of previews!
